      "content": "You are absolutely right that your body has already fought the battle, but antibiotics work by killing the specific bacteria causing the infection, not by healing the wound itself. If you stop now, you risk leaving behind a small number of survivors that can multiply and cause a much more severe, resistant infection later. The full 10-day course is a safety net to ensure those last few stubborn bacteria die off completely, so please finish the remaining pills to stay safe.",
